1
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:05,400
<i> I made a mistake.</i>

2
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:09,133
<i>The last time Thea and I
were together,</i>

3
00:00:09,267 --> 00:00:11,133
<i> Dad, Jobert saw us.</i>

4
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,867
<i> Fix this, Paolo.</i>

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,733
<i>Ashley, where do you think
you're going?</i>

6
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,967
<i>I'm going to give this
to Auntie Marj.</i>

7
00:00:19,100 --> 00:00:21,000
<i>- Give me that.
- Why, Mom?</i>

8
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:22,600
<i> Don't ask too many questions!</i>

9
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> I won't open the phone.</i>

10
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,500
<i> This belongs to Jobert, right?</i>

11
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> Why do you have it?</i>

12
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>How did it end up with Edward?
You should have stopped it.</i>

13
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>Do you want him to suspect us?
That alone would expose us.</i>

14
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:35,767
<i>Ashley gave it to me.
You might want to have it.</i>

15
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,067
Ashley.

16
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,433
Where do you think you're going?

17
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:32,867
I was just going
to the hospital, Mom.

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,067
I was just going to visit Jas
and give this to Auntie Marj.

19
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:41,400
Maybe there's a playlist
Uncle Jobert likes on this.

20
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:42,967
If he hears it,

21
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:47,133
maybe it will help him recover
and get better.

22
00:01:47,267 --> 00:01:48,433
Give me that!

23
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,133
Why, Mom?

24
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:52,233
Stop asking questions!

25
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:53,967
Go back to your room
and do your homework!

26
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:56,100
- I'll handle this.
- That belongs to Uncle Jobert.

27
00:01:56,233 --> 00:01:57,967
Just do as I say!

28
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:01,867
Go upstairs!

29
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:13,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

30
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:16,000
Am I a bad person?

31
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:20,967
Why do misfortunes keeps coming
on me?

32
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,233
It feels like heaven
is punishing me.

33
00:02:24,367 --> 00:02:27,733
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:29,833
Jobert will not leave you.

35
00:02:30,867 --> 00:02:32,367
God is good.

36
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:35,367
[Speaking in Visayan]

37
00:02:42,467 --> 00:02:44,733
Jobert...

38
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:48,433
Wake up now.

39
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:13,900
Finally, Lalaine.
I can finally breathe easily.

40
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:19,300
Now all I have to do is delete
all the videos Jobert recorded

41
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,367
of Paolo and me together.

42
00:03:21,533 --> 00:03:22,733
Hurry up, friend!

43
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:25,200
Delete it before
more evidence is found!

44
00:03:27,867 --> 00:03:29,000
Damn it.

45
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,233
Why?

46
00:03:31,367 --> 00:03:33,500
I can't open the phone!

47
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,633
Oh no, friend,
you have no choice.

48
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:39,967
Destroy it. Then delete it.

49
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:42,167
Someone else might get something
from it. Hurry up!

50
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,467
Throw it away!

51
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,300
Fine. I'll call you back.

52
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,633
This belongs to Jobert.
Why do you have it?

53
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,733
This is Jobert's?

54
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:09,533
I didn't know.
Ashley found it in the garden.

55
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:10,900
Look.

56
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:13,400
Jobert is the only one
who likes turtles here.

57
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:16,533
He probably dropped it on
the night of the accident.

58
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:19,300
I'll take this.
I'll bring it to Marj.

59
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:20,533
No need.

60
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:24,767
I'll just have the maids
bring it when they bring food.

61
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,267
- No, no, no.
- I'll do it.

62
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:27,433
I'm leaving anyway.

63
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,033
I'll give an update about
the search to Marj's mom.

64
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:30,800
No. I said I'll do it.
I can handle this.

65
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:32,333
- I'll just bring it along.
- Give it to me.

66
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:33,633
- Why won't you give it?
- Give it...

67
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,700
Wait.

68
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:40,100
What happened to you?

69
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:42,967
Since Jobert's accident
you didn't even visit him.

70
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:46,000
And now, you're insisting
on going to him?

71
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:47,467
What's going on?

72
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,900
Give it to me.

73
00:04:51,033 --> 00:05:01,000
[INTENSE MUSIC]

74
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:13,600
[PHONE RINGING]

75
00:05:13,733 --> 00:05:15,167
What?

76
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:18,933
Didn't I tell you not to call me
because I'm watching Jasmine?

77
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:20,867
We have a big problem.

78
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,200
Edward got Jobert's phone

79
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,967
and he's going to give it
to Marj.

80
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:29,567
How did it end up with Edward?

81
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,867
You should have stopped it.

82
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,167
And then what?

83
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:34,467
Do you want him
to get suspicious?

84
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:36,233
That alone would expose us.

85
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:39,833
Marj must not see that phone.

86
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:43,133
There might be videos there that
could ruin the both of us.

87
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:45,667
That's why I called you, Paolo.

88
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:49,367
Do whatever you have to do
so Marj won't open the phone.

89
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:52,133
I can't just leave Jasmine.

90
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:55,733
Then leave her
with a nurse for now.

91
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:59,900
Paolo, both our marriages
are at stake.

92
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:03,867
If you don't act,
we'll both lose our families.

93
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:13,967
[INTENSE MUSIC]

94
00:06:15,033 --> 00:06:19,033
Thank you, Edward.
You brought Pong here.

95
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:23,167
Jobert, wake up. Pong is here.

96
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:25,167
Wake up. He's waiting for you.

97
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,967
He wants to play with you.

98
00:06:29,567 --> 00:06:31,600
Marj,

99
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:35,133
I have good news
that I think will cheer you up.

100
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:37,533
I have a friend
who's an investigator.

101
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:40,000
There are records showing
your mother went to Cebu.

102
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,800
We'll look for her there.

103
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,500
Thank you, Edward.

104
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:47,500
She really needs to know
Jobert's condition

105
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:49,733
so she can come here.

106
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:52,867
I know my brother
is waiting for her.

107
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,167
By the way, Marj.

108
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,533
I almost forgot.

109
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,667
Ashley gave this.

110
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,833
You might want to have it.

111
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:05,967
[INTENSE MUSIC]

112
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:09,233
Love, what are you doing here?

113
00:07:09,367 --> 00:07:10,933
Did something happen to Jasmine?

114
00:07:11,067 --> 00:07:16,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC]

115
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,633
Nothing.

116
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:21,967
I just wanted to check on
the two of you and Jobert.

117
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:24,100
I didn't know you had a visitor.

118
00:07:25,367 --> 00:07:28,500
Well, Marj, play Jobert's turtle
videos ni Jobert.

119
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:32,200
If he hears them,
it might help him wake up.

120
00:07:32,533 --> 00:07:34,133
Don't.

121
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:35,433
Don't, love.

122
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:36,633
Why?

123
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:37,867
Is there a problem?

124
00:07:39,933 --> 00:07:44,367
I just thought Jobert might get
more stressed by the noise.

125
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:46,600
I'll keep it low.

126
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:48,800
The doctor also mentioned to me

127
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:52,267
that it's good for him to hear
familiar sounds.

128
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,900
It could stimulate his senses.

129
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:56,233
Let's try.

130
00:07:56,367 --> 00:08:04,167
[INTENSE MUSIC]

131
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:09,900
[LOW BATTERY CHIMES]

132
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,100
Too bad, it's dead.

133
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:19,700
Marj, maybe you want to charge
the cellphone.

134
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,367
Maybe your mom is calling
or texting Jobert.

135
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,667
Our chargers are different.

136
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,200
But you're right,
maybe they've been talking.

137
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:31,033
Hannah, when you come back,

138
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,767
can you bring Jobert's charger
here?

139
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,967
Of course, dear.

140
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,433
Thank you.

141
00:08:37,567 --> 00:08:39,333
All right, Marj, I'll go ahead.

142
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,433
Thanks again.

143
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:51,333
Love, are you okay?

144
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:52,767
Yes, love.

145
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:55,233
I probably
just haven't slept much.

146
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:11,467
Go on, answer it.

147
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:22,433
Hello, Mom.

148
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,467
Paolo, I'll just remind you.

149
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:27,267
Tomorrow is the renewal of vows
with your dad.

150
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,500
You need to be there.

151
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:31,500
Our friends and business
partners will expect to see you.

152
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:34,800
Mom, please.
You know I'm at the hospital.

153
00:09:34,933 --> 00:09:37,067
And I can't just leave Marj.

154
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,567
Especially since Jobert
hasn't woken up.

155
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:42,433
And Jasmine just finished
her chemo infusion.

156
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:44,133
She's still weak.

157
00:09:44,267 --> 00:09:46,833
Paolo, it's just one night.

158
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:48,600
I mean, there's a nurse anyway.

159
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,767
This is a milestone
for our family.

160
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:54,167
Don't embarrass your dad
in front of our guests.

161
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:57,600
Just a couple of hours.
Please do this for me.

162
00:09:57,733 --> 00:09:59,400
Sorry, Mom.

163
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:01,967
But I can't leave my family.

164
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:07,600
I have to go now, bye.

165
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:08,900
Paolo?

166
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:15,933
[INTENSE MUSIC]

167
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:18,233
Love.

168
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:22,067
Go on, give in to your mom.
Go tomorrow.

169
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,033
Love, your brother
is still in a coma.

170
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:28,133
Jasmine just finished
her chemo infusion.

171
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:30,300
This is not the right time
to celebrate.

172
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,300
Paolo, it's not a party
you're going to.

173
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:36,967
Family.

174
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:40,567
And I don't want to add
to your mom's anger toward me.

175
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:43,667
I don't want this
to become a big issue.

176
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:48,667
Because of me,
her plans will be ruined.

177
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,967
So please, please. Go.

178
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,700
I can handle this.

179
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:57,500
I'll watch Jobert and Jasmine.
Hannah is here to help me.

180
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:59,267
Please, go.

181
00:11:00,933 --> 00:11:02,033
All right.

182
00:11:02,167 --> 00:11:06,267
Okay, I'll attend.
But I won't stay long.

183
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,633
Thank you.

184
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:17,767
[INTENSE MUSIC]

185
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:28,633
Something's bothering you.

186
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:30,433
I've seen that face.

187
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,767
When....

188
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:36,600
something happened between...

189
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,133
you and Thea before.

190
00:11:47,433 --> 00:11:48,667
So, tell me.

191
00:11:56,067 --> 00:11:58,567
For Christ's sake, Paolo,

192
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,467
speak!

193
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,000
I thought you already learned?

194
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:06,467
You even promised
it wouldn't happen again.

195
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,267
I made a mistake.

196
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:14,000
It happened when Marj and I
were drifting apart.

197
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,867
I really planned to end it.

198
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:20,667
But then...

199
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,733
But then what?

200
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:25,567
But then...

201
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:29,533
the last time...

202
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:31,267
Thea and I were together,

203
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:34,567
Dad, Jobert saw us.

204
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:40,367
It was the reason...

205
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:44,167
he was upset that night...

206
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,067
and why he got into an accident.

207
00:12:51,167 --> 00:12:52,400
Dad.

208
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,200
Dad, I'm sorry.

209
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,667
I'm sorry.

210
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,333
What did you expect?

211
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:10,967
I'm the one who has to clean up
your mess again?

212
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:14,667
I've had it with you, Paolo.

213
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:21,633
I didn't raise you
to be a failure...

214
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,800
like your sibling.

215
00:13:25,867 --> 00:13:27,867
Fix this, Paolo.

216
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,900
Make sure it doesn't blow up.

217
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:34,133
Because if it does,

218
00:13:34,267 --> 00:13:37,433
our family will be destroyed.

219
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:50,567
The cell phone
is on Jobert's side table.

220
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:53,667
Take it and give it to me, okay?

221
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,333
Okay, Sir. When I get there,
I'll tell Ma'am Marj.

222
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,500
Don't!

223
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:02,300
- Is this already complete?
- Yes, it's good for one week.

224
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:03,567
Okay.

225
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:04,700
All right.

226
00:14:05,433 --> 00:14:09,500
Marj must not know about this.
No one should see you.

227
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,000
Why, Sir?

228
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:16,033
If you don't want to lose
your job, just follow my order.

229
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,333
Do you understand?

230
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,233
Yes, Sir. I'll handle it.

231
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:31,333
[INTENSE MUSIC]

232
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:37,067
I feel so sorry for you, Jobert.

233
00:14:46,933 --> 00:14:48,133
I'll go to the pharmacy,

234
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:51,200
then I'll just leave this at the
nursing station for you, okay?

235
00:14:51,533 --> 00:14:53,033
Okay, I'll just come back later

236
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,833
to check if all the medicines
are complete.

237
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:56,400
Okay.

238
00:14:56,533 --> 00:15:03,733
[INTENSE MUSIC]

239
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:04,967
Cell phone.

240
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:15,067
[INTENSE MUSIC]

241
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:21,567
Oscar?

242
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,267
What are you doing?

243
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,133
Ma'am, there's...

244
00:15:29,267 --> 00:15:31,700
Sir Paolo asked me
to look for something.

245
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:35,367
He couldn't leave the mansion.
They're preparing for an event.

246
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:37,700
What is he looking for?

247
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:42,000
His credit card case.
He said it's missing.

248
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:44,300
Maybe he left it here

249
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:47,167
and you might have put it
with Jobert's belongings.

250
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,367
I didn't see anything
he left behind,

251
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,333
even in Jasmine's room.

252
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:55,367
It's fine. If I find it,
I'll just call him, okay?

253
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,300
Okay, Ma'am.
All right, I'll go now.

254
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:13,300
Where is my lipstick?

255
00:16:15,067 --> 00:16:16,700
Where is that lipstick?

256
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,300
Hey, hey, hey. Thea, Thea.

257
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:22,800
What's the problem?

258
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:26,567
Why do you seem agitated today?

259
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:29,167
I'm fine.
What are you talking about?

260
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,067
Hon.

261
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,267
I know you.

262
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,467
I know when something's
bothering you.

263
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,833
So, tell me. What is it?

264
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:43,533
Sir, I searched for
the cellphone on the table

265
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:46,533
and also in the drawer
but I didn't find it.

266
00:16:46,667 --> 00:16:50,767
Then you should've searched
the whole room!

267
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:54,333
That was the plan, Sir.
But Ma'am Marj arrived.

268
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:55,800
I just made an excuse.

269
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:57,967
What's wrong with you, Oscar?

270
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:02,100
I specifically told you
to be seen, right?

271
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:06,500
I witnessed Jobert's accident.

272
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:09,000
And now we have to smile

273
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:13,733
and celebrate the renewal
of vows of Mom and Dad.

274
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,467
As if nothing happened.

275
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:19,167
Isn't that stressful?

276
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:23,067
And on top of that,
I can't find my lipstick.

277
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,000
Hey, hon.

278
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:28,600
I'm sorry. Okay?

279
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:32,833
I didn't realize how deep the
impact of what happened on you.

280
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:40,500
I'll go downstairs.

281
00:17:40,633 --> 00:17:42,867
Maybe the lipstick
is just in the car.

282
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:50,733
I'm really sorry, Sir.

283
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:55,633
But it seems Ma'am Marj believed
my excuse.

284
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:58,167
Oscar, bottom line,
you still failed!

285
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,967
I gave you a very simple task!

286
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,700
Get out of my sight!

287
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:12,800
[INTENSE MUSIC]

288
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,767
Oscar looks nervous when I saw
him earlier.

289
00:18:17,967 --> 00:18:20,967
I don't want to doubt anymore,

290
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,167
but my gut strongly tells me

291
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:24,433
that he's not telling me
the truth.

292
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:32,933
Do you think he's looking for
something?

293
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:39,433
Did you bring Jobert's charger?

294
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:40,533
Of course, dear.

295
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:43,333
Good thing Jobert and I
use the same charger.

296
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:48,733
Thank you.

297
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:58,167
There, it's on.

298
00:19:01,033 --> 00:19:02,233
Jobert?

299
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:08,167
Your brother Edward told me
that Mom might be found soon.

300
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:10,833
Here, he brought your cellphone.

301
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:12,667
But while she's not here yet,

302
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:18,867
let's watch Mom's videos
so you can hear her voice.

303
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:39,767
Ashley and Jobert
are so cute together.

304
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:42,800
He was still so lively
that night, right?

305
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,367
Looks like Jobert has new
videos.

306
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:55,733
Here, Pong. There.

307
00:19:57,767 --> 00:20:02,467
Let's send this to Baby Jasmine,
Pong.

308
00:20:02,633 --> 00:20:08,333
Jobert will send this to
Baby Jasmine so she'll be happy.

309
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:17,667
Oh, my goodness!

310
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,467
This is not real.

311
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,500
Their faces are clearly visible!
This is awful!

312
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:38,000
You shameless people!

313
00:20:39,733 --> 00:20:42,567
How could they do this to me?

314
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:45,767
My God, Paolo and Thea.

315
00:20:48,767 --> 00:20:51,767
Watch over Jobert and Jasmine
here.

316
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,233
Marj, Marj, wait.
Calm down first.

317
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:55,067
Don't act impulsively.

318
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,900
How can I calm down?

319
00:20:57,667 --> 00:21:02,433
My child is already seriously
ill, and they're betraying me!

320
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:06,333
Maybe this is the reason why my
brother got into an accident!

321
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:09,533
I won't allow them
to make a fool of me again!

322
00:21:10,533 --> 00:21:13,533
I will put an end to their
filth!

323
00:21:13,667 --> 00:21:15,300
Marj!

324
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:17,333
Wait, just wait Marj!

325
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:27,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

326
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:35,500
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

327
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:36,867
What now?

328
00:21:38,967 --> 00:21:40,367
I didn't get it.

329
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,867
It's still with her.

330
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:43,667
What?

331
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,067
So, what now?

332
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,267
Where is Marj?

333
00:21:48,333 --> 00:21:51,067
Paolo, I'm getting nervous.

334
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:52,100
Hon.

335
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:54,967
Isn't this show starting yet?

336
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:58,600
It's probably about to start.

337
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,067
Come on, let's sit down.

338
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:11,167
[INTENSE MUSIC]

339
00:22:18,667 --> 00:22:22,367
People always say that marriage
is about sacrifice.

340
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,133
To be a good wife,

341
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:28,333
they say,
you must always endure.

342
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:31,567
But you know what, Greg?

343
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:39,533
I don't think I need to always
stay silent or play the martyr.

344
00:22:40,833 --> 00:22:42,800
Because sometimes,

345
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:46,167
you have to be the loudest
person in the room

346
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:48,367
to keep the walls from falling.

347
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:58,467
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

348
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:04,067
A home
isn't just about architecture.

349
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:08,333
It's not just beautiful design,
expensive chandeliers,

350
00:23:08,467 --> 00:23:11,033
or imported sofas.

351
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:15,600
In a home, you should be safe.

352
00:23:16,867 --> 00:23:19,367
Safe from deception

353
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:24,467
and safe from lies.

354
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:29,200
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

355
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:34,200
Because the moment you let lies
through your door,

356
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:36,767
no matter how beautiful
your house is,

357
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:39,000
it becomes a prison.

358
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:45,667
A prison for the people
you claim to love.

359
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:58,167
And that is why
we are here today.

360
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:04,100
That is why this house
is so important.

361
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:13,600
[INTENSE MUSIC]

362
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,000
Greg,

363
00:24:16,333 --> 00:24:22,067
it is living proof
of our strength.

364
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:27,033
I'm not just renewing
marriage vows,

365
00:24:27,167 --> 00:24:30,100
I'm renewing my vow
to this home.

366
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:36,600
Because I will not allow anyone
to destroy it.

367
00:24:40,333 --> 00:24:42,733
Because at all costs,

368
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:45,200
I will fight for this home.

369
00:24:46,233 --> 00:24:50,233
I will fight for us.

370
00:24:50,367 --> 00:25:00,333
[INTENSE MUSIC]

371
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:23,467
[INTENSE MUSIC]

372
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,800
<i>- Are we okay?
- What do you mean?</i>

373
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:30,100
<i> Even when we're together,
you feel distant from me lately.</i>

374
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:35,633
<i>You know,
men like Paolo and his father</i>

375
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,600
<i>don't say
when they're pulling away.</i>

376
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:40,767
<i>When they don't get
the attention</i>

377
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:43,367
<i>they're looking for from their
wives,</i>

378
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:46,367
<i>that's when they will start
looking elsewhere.</i>

379
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:47,900
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

380
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:50,333
<i> I wanted to surprise you.</i>

381
00:25:50,467 --> 00:25:52,967
<i>I didn't know I would
be the one surprised.</i>

382
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:54,967
<i>Why did the staff leave this
open?</i>

383
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:58,100
<i> Marj!</i>

384
00:25:58,233 --> 00:25:59,167
<i> Hello?</i>

385
00:26:00,567 --> 00:26:02,133
<i>- Love.
- Are you at the office?</i>

386
00:26:02,267 --> 00:26:03,700
<i> Office. In a meeting.</i>

387
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,900
<i> You shameless people!</i>

388
00:26:19,033 --> 00:26:27,033
[INTENSE MUSIC]

389
00:26:27,167 --> 00:26:35,067
I thought the home I entered was
strong, happy, and perfect.

390
00:26:37,933 --> 00:26:40,667
But everything
was just an illusion.

391
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:44,567
The foundation of this house
is not stone,

392
00:26:44,733 --> 00:26:46,833
but lies.

393
00:26:53,767 --> 00:26:56,167
Stop this nonsense now!

394
00:26:56,300 --> 00:26:58,467
You did not have any right

395
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:01,933
to turn a private family matter
into a public spectacle!

396
00:27:02,067 --> 00:27:04,267
What are you so angry
about that you made a scene?

397
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,100
Why did you ruin my day?

398
00:27:06,233 --> 00:27:08,667
There was an earlier scandal.

399
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,700
You promised
a stable relationship!

400
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,400
How dare you have the nerve!

401
00:27:13,533 --> 00:27:15,233
How long
have you been fooling me?

402
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,367
How long did you lie to me?

403
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:21,133
Our family will be destroyed
because of you!
